  You do not currently need a visa to come to the UK
<% end %>

<% govspeak_for :body do %>
  You do not need a visa to get married or enter into a civil partnership in the UK if you come to the UK on or before 30 June 2021.

  However, you should bring the [same documents](/government/publications/visitor-visa-guide-to-supporting-documents) you’d need to apply for a Standard Visitor visa, to show officers at the UK border.

  If you come to the UK from 1 July 2021, you’ll need to apply for a [Marriage Visitor visa](/marriage-visa).

  ##If you want to live in the UK permanently

  You can apply for a [family of a settled person visa](/join-family-in-uk) if your partner is any of the following:

  + is a British citizen
  + is settled in the UK (called having ‘indefinite leave to remain’)
  + has settled or pre-settled status under the EU Settlement Scheme
  + has a Turkish worker or businessperson visa

  ##If you want to convert a civil partnership into a marriage

  You do not need a visa. However, you should bring the [same documents](/government/publications/visitor-visa-guide-to-supporting-documents) you’d need to apply for a Standard Visitor visa, to show officers at the UK border.
<% end %>
